Dirty Air Filter
A category representing an issue where accumulated dirt on the air filter obstructs airflow, causing poor cooling performance.

Low Refrigerant
A category indicating insufficient refrigerant levels due to leaks or improper charging, leading to inadequate cooling.

Faulty Capacitor
A category describing a malfunction in the capacitor unit, affecting the AC's ability to start and maintain operation.

No Power to Unit
A category denoting issues where electrical power isn't reaching the AC system, preventing it from turning on.

Faulty Thermostat
A category referring to problems with the thermostat's functionality, such as not sending signals to activate the AC unit.

Failed Transformer
A category indicating a malfunction in the transformer, which is crucial for providing power to various components of the AC system.

AC Unit
The AC unit is the central device in question, experiencing issues such as failure to cool, failure to turn on, or making loud noises.

Indoor Unit
The indoor unit of an AC system, which includes components like air filters and blowers responsible for circulating cooled air within a space.

Outdoor Unit (Condenser)
The outdoor component of an AC system that expels heat from the refrigerant, essential for cooling functionality.

Air Filter
A replaceable or reusable part of the indoor unit that captures airborne particles to prevent them from circulating in the air and potentially damaging the AC system.

Refrigerant
The substance used in AC systems to absorb heat from the environment and transfer it outside, enabling cooling functionality.

Capacitor
An electrical component that stores energy to assist in starting and running the AC unit's motor; failure can prevent proper operation.

Thermostat
A device used to regulate temperature settings, ensuring the AC unit operates according to programmed or manual instructions.

Transformer
An electrical component that steps down voltage to power low-voltage components of the AC system; failure can disrupt operation.

Circuit Breaker
A safety device in an electrical panel that can be tripped, interrupting power supply to the AC unit and preventing it from operating.

Disconnect Switch
An outdoor component used to manually turn off power to the AC system for maintenance or safety purposes.

Technical Troubleshooting
A category related to diagnosing and resolving technical issues in air conditioning systems.

Debris in Fan
A situation where foreign objects such as leaves or twigs cause noise by obstructing the fan blades.

Worn Fan Motor Bearings
A condition where the motor bearings are worn out, leading to grinding noises and potential failure of the fan motor.

Loose Components
A scenario where parts of the AC unit are not securely fastened, resulting in rattling or vibrating noises.
